def_cn: 早起的鸟儿有虫吃；捷足先登
def_en: If you say that the early bird catches the worm, you mean that the person who arrives first in a place is most likely to get what they want.

def_cn: 早行动的人;(尤指)早起的人
def_en: An early bird is someone who does something or goes somewhere very early, especially very early in the morning.
An early bird deal or offer is one that is available at a reduced price, but which you must buy earlier than you would normally do.
